Type: This amendment is made in response to the July 24, 2022 Request for Additional Information (RFAI) for the following items identified in that letter:     1.       The Committee reviewed all the contributions identified in the RFAI. For apparently excessive contributions, the Committee seeks re-attributions whenever possible within the 60 day window, or refunds the contribution. As the RFAI notes, the Committee explains its corrective actions as a reporting description for contributions that appear excessive on the report. Certain refunds or re-attributions will reflect on the Committee's October Quarterly report.    2.       This contribution was refunded. The refund will reflect on the October Quarterly report.    3.       This amendment fixes the Summary and Detailed Summary Page calculations that did not correctly reflect due to a software issue.    4.       The transaction identified was part of a re-attribution that did not correctly reflect due to a software issue. This amendment properly reflects the re-attribution.    5.       The Committee did report the original contribution when received. The refund to David Deitch should have been designated to P2022 and this amendment reflects that designation. Roberta Khun's original $125 contribution was unitemized. One of the refunds to Hank O'Donnell has been amended to reflect proper designation to P2022.    6.       The contribution identified in the RFAI was never received. The contribution inadvertently reported as a contribution from the Council for a Livable World Candidate Fund on a 48-hour report was an earmarked contribution that was already received and reported on the pre-primary report from Lynne Horning. The Committee amended the applicable 48-hour report to remove this contribution. As such, it was properly not included on this report.    7.       As with item 4, the transaction identified was part of a re-attribution that did not correctly reflect due to a software issue. This amendment properly reflects the re-attribution.    8.       The amendment discloses the inadvertently omitted debt and properly reflects its payment on this amendment.
